    • containsTagsWithChildren

      public static boolean containsTagsWithChildren​(org.w3c.dom.Document document, java.lang.String requiredParentTagName, int requiredNumberOfParents, java.lang.String requiredChildrenTagName, @Nullable java.lang.String requiredChildrenValue)
      Parameters:
      document - The source to be parsed
      requiredParentTagName - Parent tagName to be created or an existing one
      requiredNumberOfParents - How many parents with the desired child should be presented within the given document
      requiredChildrenTagName - Parent's children tagName that should be presented strictly within parent's tag
      requiredChildrenValue - If not null, what exact text value should those children have. Otherwise will be ignored. And only num of parents and children tag name will be considered.
      Returns:
      True if all the conditions are valid
